#: ../../soundalike-slang.rst:5
msgid "Soundalike Slang"
msgstr "語呂合わせスラング"

#: ../../soundalike-slang.rst:7
msgid ""
"Hackers will often make rhymes or puns in order to convert an ordinary word "
"or phrase into something more interesting. It is considered particularly "
":ref:`flavorful` if the phrase is bent so as to include some other jargon "
"word; thus the computer hobbyist magazine *Dr. Dobb'sJournal* is almost "
"always referred to among hackers as ‘Dr. Frob's Journal’ or simply ‘Dr. "
"Frob's’. Terms of this kind that have been in fairly wide use include names "
"for newspapers:"
msgstr ""
"ハッカーは、ありふれた単語や句をもっと面白いものに変えるために、よく韻を踏んだり地口を言ったりする。その句が何か別のジャーゴン語を含むように曲げられていると、特に\\"
" :ref:`flavorful`\\ だと見なされる。したがって、コンピューター愛好家の雑誌\\ *Dr. Dobb'sJournal*\\ "
"は、ハッカーの間ではほとんど常に‘Dr. Frob's Journal’あるいは単に‘Dr. "
"Frob's’と呼ばれる。この種の語でかなり広く使われてきたものには、新聞の名前が含まれる。"

#: ../../soundalike-slang.rst:13
msgid "Boston Herald → Horrid (or Harried)"
msgstr "Boston Herald → Horrid(または Harried)"

#: ../../soundalike-slang.rst:15
msgid "Boston Globe → Boston Glob"
msgstr "Boston Globe → Boston Glob"

#: ../../soundalike-slang.rst:17
msgid "Houston (or San Francisco) Chronicle → the Crocknicle (or the Comical)"
msgstr "Houston(または San Francisco)Chronicle → the Crocknicle(または the Comical)"

#: ../../soundalike-slang.rst:19
msgid "New York Times → New York Slime"
msgstr "New York Times → New York Slime"

#: ../../soundalike-slang.rst:21
msgid "Wall Street Journal → Wall Street Urinal"
msgstr "Wall Street Journal → Wall Street Urinal"

#: ../../soundalike-slang.rst:23
msgid ""
"However, terms like these are often made up on the spur of the moment. "
"Standard examples include:"
msgstr "しかし、これらのような語はとっさにその場で作られることが多い。標準的な例には次のものがある。"

